Small example. This one will list hosts like '*test*', limited only by 
access level for API user. So, remember to add user to appropriate groups 
and assign enought permissions.

use Net::Zabbix;

my $z = Net::Zabbix->new("http://server/zabbix", "API", "calvin", 1);
# no need to specify at each call
$z->output("extended"); 
my $r = $z->get("host", {
		filter => undef,
        search => {
            host => "test",
        },
	}
);

Consult Zabbix API documentation for details.
- http://www.zabbix.com/wiki/doc/api 
- http://www.zabbix.com/documentation/1.8/api
